Description:
   Seam Snare is an advanced trap-setting technique unique to the Cipher.
   The operative exploits structural seams — gaps between surfaces, cracks
   in floors, doorway thresholds — to place a nearly invisible snare that
   triggers when an opponent passes through. The snare entangles the target,
   immobilizing them briefly and leaving them vulnerable to attack.

   Unlike conventional traps, the Seam Snare is placed with such precision
   that it is extremely difficult to detect. The snare material is threaded
   through existing environmental gaps, meaning it leaves no visible
   apparatus. The Cipher can then position themselves for an ambush or simply
   use the immobilization to create distance if they need to escape. The
   snare can only catch one target before it must be re-set.
